' NOTE: The modeling of ElectricVehicle is incomplete inside the Energy Grid ontology:
' - ElectricVehicle lives under Ontology/Prosumers/ in the energy grid ontology
' - Authors modeled it as a consumer/producer of energy
' - Has a dangling relationship with EVChargingStation (From Smart City ontology)
' - No relationship to energy grid entities like UsagePoint, CustomerLoad, EquivalentLoad, etc.

@startuml Energy Grid Electric Vehicle

' NOTE: EVChargingStation is referenced here for cross-domain linkage,
' but it is not defined in the Energy Grid ontology. It belongs to the Smart City ontology.
entity EVChargingStation <<bridge>> {
}

' Adapted from CIM and https://github.com/smart-data-models/dataModel.EnergyCIM/ data models: an electric vehicle model
' An electric vehicle (EV) is a vehicle that uses one or more electric motors or traction motors for propulsion.
' An electric vehicle may be powered through a collector system by electricity from off-vehicle sources,
' or may be self-contained with a battery, solar panels, fuel cells or an electric generator to convert fuel to electricity.
'
' <<key>> decision:
' - **`ElectricVehicle`** — the demand side of the problem. Its `chargeRateMax` sets the upper bound on which station power levels are compatible, `chargeTarget` quantifies how much energy is needed, and `chargeTargetTimestamp` establishes urgency. Without these, no assignment decision can be made.
entity ElectricVehicle <<key>> {
    evName: string /' The name of the electric vehicle. '/
    capacity: double /' Total EV battery capacity. '/
    ' chargeMin: double /' Minimum charge limit. '/
    chargeRateMin: double /' Minimum charging rate. '/
    chargeRateMax: double /' Maximum charging rate. '/
    ' dischargeRateMin: double /' Minimum discharge rate. '/
    ' dischargeRateMax: double /' Maximum discharge rate. '/
    chargeTarget: double /' Target capacity to be charged '/
    chargeTargetTimestamp: dateTime /' Target end datetime to be charged '/
    ' -- connectedTo_ChargingStation --> EVChargingStation /' EV --> ChargingStation '/
}

ElectricVehicle --> EVChargingStation : connectedTo_ChargingStation /' EV --> ChargingStation '/

note right of EVChargingStation
Not defined in Energy Grid;
belongs to Smart City ontology.
end note

@enduml
